review_blob: after a hundred or so beers this is my favorite.  I found one of these while visiting family in tennessee.  Only beer the store sold.  I had just got back from dining out and had 3 pints of sierra nevada and was welcomed with this beauty.  Since then I have ordered 24 from california.  Anyway, smells of malt, tastes smokey for a hoppy beer.  Tons of flavor, read below.
I drink this when it's on special out of the tap.  It's not too bad.  A very watered down example of a good beer.  Decent head, decent lacing but an ashtray taste.
I'm not a big fan of this although it's the best they have at don pablos.  Kind of like a killians but not near as deep.

I always get the urge to drink a vew of these every now and again.  I drink em straiht out of the bottle because I like the way it comes out.  A fashion, showy beer for when everyone is drinking macros.  I buy the 24oz ones at the gas station once in a while.
the very worst. I'd rather have malt liqour all day.  Drank this maybe a couple times in high school but was lucky enough to drin better macros.

I really liked this beer.  It's very sweet and loaded with carmel/malt.  very, very easy to drink.  Although I think after 3 I would want something with more bite. Thin head, very little mouthfeel (although slightly creamy.... not heavy).  will order again for sure.
I gove this the same I gave bud light.  I would prefer this in a bottle and bud out of a keg.  I stay away from both of them now.  If it's 75 cent domestic pints I usually go for this.
yes, it is a terible beer but the best of the macro lights (menaing the most water like).  Lowest alcohol % too of course.  So easy to drink, expecially out of a keg.  I'm glad I never liked this.

this is one of my favorite beers that is easy to get t the supermarket.  Great dark, thick flavor for an american macro.  Just love the taste of this beer.  Either this os sierra nevada is what i go for.  pure white, pretty quick diminishing head.  Wonderful mouthfeel for a american macro with 4.7% alcohol.  Yum.

I found it to be a decent amber.  It has a small head but a fair amount of lacing.  Very tart/citrusy 1st go but after that it just got boring.  It was pretty highly carbonated too.  Decent, won't buy again.
